# Walkthrough - Sakakibara Tax Website

## Overview
I have successfully designed and implemented the top page for **Sakakibara Tax Accountant Office**. The website is built with semantic HTML and professional CSS, adhering to the specified design requirements and color palette.

## Changes
- **Project Setup**: Created [index.html](file:///c:/Users/hangy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/sakakibara-tax01/index.html) and [style.css](file:///c:/Users/hangy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/sakakibara-tax01/style.css).
- **Assets**: Integrated the logo.
- **Design Implementation**:
    - **Color Palette**: Deep Navy (#1F2A44), Gold (#BDAA4B), Warm Gray (#F4F4F2).
    - **Sections**: Implemented all 10 requested sections including First View, Problem/Empathy, Strengths, Services, Voice, Representative Message, Columns, Flow, Contact, and Access.
    - **Responsiveness**: Fully responsive design for Mobile (375px), Tablet (768px), and Desktop (1440px).

## Verification Results

### Responsive Design Check
I verified the website on multiple device sizes to ensure no layout issues or overflow.

- **Desktop (1440px)**: All sections are aligned, hover effects work, and the layout spans the full width correctly.
- **Tablet (768px)**: The 3-column layouts stack appropriately, and the hamburger menu appears and functions.
- **Mobile (375px)**: No horizontal scroll (overflow). Text is readable, and navigation is accessible via the hamburger menu.

